Gary Lineker has taken to Twitter to give his reaction to Nottingham Forest winning promotion to the Premier League and is looking forward to Leicester City playing against them. The former Leicester striker and Match of the Day presenter is pleased to see former European champions Nottingham Forest back in the Premier League. Forest have won promotion from the Championship to the Premier League via the playoffs. -Advertisement- The Reds got the better of Huddersfield Town 1-0 at Wembley Stadium in London in the Championship playoff final on Sunday. An own goal from Levi Colwill in the first half proved to be the difference between the two teams. Former Forest player Ben Osborn, now at Sheffield United, is also pleased for the City Ground faithful.